---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Legal Notice — OpenPolicy"
	description="OpenPolicy generates policy documents from your configuration. It is not a substitute for legal advice."
	ogUrl="https://openpolicy.sh/legal-notice"
>
	<section>
		<h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">LEGAL.md</h2>
		<article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
			<h1>Legal Notice</h1>

			<p>
				<strong
					>OpenPolicy generates policy documents from your configuration. It
					does not provide legal advice.</strong
				>
			</p>

			<p>
				The documents, components, and defaults produced by OpenPolicy — including
				any templates, presets, and jurisdiction-specific supplements — are
				provided for general informational purposes only. They are not a
				substitute for advice from a qualified lawyer licensed in your
				jurisdiction.
			</p>

			<p>
				Privacy, cookie, and data-protection obligations depend on the specific
				data you collect, the services you integrate, the regions your users
				are in, the contracts you have in place, and the way you operate your
				business. No automated tool can resolve those facts for you. You are
				responsible for the policies you publish and the practices they
				describe.
			</p>

			<h2>Before you publish</h2>

			<p>
				Have a lawyer review your policies before they go live, and review them
				again when your product, data practices, or regulated surface changes.
				Regulators and courts look at the substance of your practices, not the
				tool that generated the document.
			</p>

			<h2>No lawyer-client relationship</h2>

			<p>
				Using OpenPolicy, reading its documentation, or communicating with its
				maintainers does not create a lawyer-client relationship. OpenPolicy
				does not provide legal services and no OpenPolicy output should be
				relied on as such.
			</p>

			<h2>No warranty</h2>

			<p>
				OpenPolicy is provided <em>as is</em>, without warranty of any kind,
				express or implied, including fitness for a particular purpose or
				compliance with any specific law or regulation. See the license terms
				in the source repository for the full disclaimer of warranties and
				limitation of liability.
			</p>

			<h2>Questions</h2>

			<p>
				For questions about OpenPolicy itself (not legal questions), contact
				<a href="mailto:jamie@openpolicy.sh">jamie@openpolicy.sh</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>Company details</h2>

			<p>
				OpenPolicy is a trading name of <strong>PolicyStack Ltd</strong>, a
				company registered in the United Kingdom.
			</p>
		</article>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
